def_cn: （变化或事件）早该发生的
def_en: If you say that a change or an event is overdue, you mean that you think it should have happened before now.

def_cn: （钱款）到期未付的，拖欠的
def_en: Overdue sums of money have not been paid, even though it is later than the date on which they should have been paid.

def_cn: （图书馆的书）逾期未还的
def_en: An overdue library book has not been returned to the library, even though the date on which it should have been returned has passed.
